        <hr/>
                        
<div class="txt-block" id="name-bio-text">
        <div class="name-trivia-bio-text">
                      <div class="inline" itemprop="description">
Paul Haggis is the award-winning filmmaker who, in 2006, became the first screenwriter to write two Best Film Oscar winners back-to-back - <a href="/title/tt0405159?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk1">Million Dollar Baby</a> (2004) directed by <a href="/name/nm0000142?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk2">Clint Eastwood</a>, and <a href="/title/tt0375679?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk3">Crash</a> (2004) which he himself directed. For <a href="/title/tt0375679?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk4">Crash</a> (2004), he won Academy Awards for Best Picture and Best Original Screenplay. The film also received ...            <span class="see-more inline nobr-only">
                    <a href="/name/nm0353673/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm"
>See full bio</a> &raquo;
            </span>
</div>        </div>
</div>

                        
    <div id="name-born-info" class="txt-block">
        <h4 class="inline">Born:</h4> 
<a href="/name/nm0353673/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bth_nm"
> Paul Edward Haggis
</a>            <br />
   
  <time datetime="1953-3-10" itemprop="birthDate">
<a href="/search/name?birth_monthday=3-10&refine=birth_monthday&ref_=nm_ov_bth_monthday"
>March 10</a>, 
     
<a href="/search/name?birth_year=1953&ref_=nm_ov_bth_year"
>1953</a>    
  </time>
            in
            <a href="/search/name?birth_place=London,+Ontario,+Canada&ref_=nm_ov_bth_place"
>London, Ontario, Canada</a>
    </div>

                        
                        
